The paper deals with codes and their properties, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Coding Theory (cs.CC) sub-categories. The use of Tur\'an graphs in the construction of codes suggests a connection to Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Distributed Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The study of Generalized Hamming Weights and minimum distance bounds also suggests a connection to Data Structures (cs.DS) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
